Madison Avenue, N.E. corner of 57th Street, 57th Street side, showing the Central Presbyterian Church, originally built in 1870 for Madison Avenue Reformed Church, remodelled in 1921 when avenue was widened. It is about to be demolished.
On N.W. corner is Bankers' Trust Building (about 1918).
May 24, 1928.

Photograph by George A. Fuller Co.
Gift of Walker & Gillette.

Madison Avenue, N.E. corner of 57th Street, looking north from S.E. corner.
The Central Presbyterian Church, originally built in 1871 for the Madison Avenue Reformed Church, and remodelled in 1921 when the avenue was widened, is about to be demolished. With the pictures of this series may be compared the view of Madison Avenue, north from 55th Street, taken in May 1871.

May 24, 1928.

Fuller Building nearing completion, Madison Avenue at N. E. corner of 57th Street.
This photograph was taken from Park Avenue at S. E. corner of 57th Street, and the view is west on 57th Street. In background, to right of new building, may be seen towers of Savoy-Plaza and Sherry Netherland hotels on Fifth Avenue.

Fuller Building nearing completion, Madison Avenue at N.E. corner of 57th Street.
In the left foreground the old Plaza Theatre has just been demolished. The view is south on Madison Avenue from 59th Street.

Fuller Building with construction work completed, Madison Avenue at N. E. corner of 57th Street, from roof adjoining corner. August (?) 6, 1929.

Photograph by George A. Fuller Co.
Gift of Walker & Gillette.

A general view north on Madison Ave. from East 57th Street. Note Central Park on the left with Central Park West dimly observable with the twin towers of the San Remo (Apartment House) thereon. Silhouetted against the Park (left foreground) is the sloped roof of the Savoy-Plaza Hotel. On the right appears the chimney of the electric generating plant of the Consolidated Gas Company (East 92nd Street at the East River).

About 1930.
